 Eight
people are missing and presumed trapped after a
five-storey hotel which was under construction at Makeji area in Murang’a County
collapsed. The eight were part of a group of 58
construction workers at the site before the building came tumbling down. Murang'a County Police Commander Donatha
Kiplang'at, confirming the Friday incident, also said there were 43 people working at
the hotel at the time of the incident. According to Ms. Kiplang’at, all 43 people have
been accounted, with only two of them being hospitalised after sustaining
injuries. “Kuna
wale ambao walikuwa kwa construction site ambao tumeelezwa kwamba walikuwa 58…mpaka
sasa, baada ya kuchukua roll call, tumeona kwamba 8 of them are missing.
Therefore we have mobilised multi-agencies to come and assist in the rescue
mission,” said the Police Commander. “We have with us the Red Cross, the National Disaster
Management, NGAO, police, fire brigade, KDF, NYS etc.” Rescue operations are presently ongoing.